# Response reporting

When a response involved creating, editing, or running code, end it with this
block exactly — after any other explanation, with every field present:

```
=== SUMMARY ===
DID: one line per action taken, files created or modified named explicitly
TESTS: pass/fail counts, or "none run"
OUTPUT: the complete terminal output, unabridged. If longer than 50 lines,
        print the first 20 and last 20 with a note about how many were cut.
BROKE: anything that failed, errored, or that you worked around. Write "nothing"
       if clean. Never omit this line.
CHOSE: any decision you made that was not specified in my prompt, and why.
       Write "nothing" if none. Never omit this line.
NEXT: what you think the next step is, one line, or "unclear"
```

## Field rules

- Always include every field, even when the value is "nothing" or "none run"
- Never summarize or truncate error messages; paste them in full
- Never claim a test passed without having actually run it
- This block goes at the very end, after any other explanation
